<img class="size-full wp-image-1534638 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ekwere.jpg?resize=590%2C744&#038;ssl=1" alt="Ekweremadu, Enugu" width="590" height="744" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ekwere.jpg?w=590&amp;ssl=1 590w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ekwere.jpg?resize=238%2C300&amp;ssl=1 238w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ekwere.jpg?resize=46%2C58&amp;ssl=1 46w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ekwere.jpg?resize=154%2C194&amp;ssl=1 154w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ekwere.jpg?resize=103%2C130&amp;ssl=1 103w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" data-recalc-dims="1" />Former Senate President, Dr Bukola Saraki, Friday sent a condolence message to former Deputy Senate President, Ike Ekweremadu, describing his late brother as a passionate public servant that served his people well. In a statement obtained by Vanguard, Saraki said: “Sending my heartfelt condolences to my friend and brother, Senator Ike Ekweremadu, on the death of his brother, the Commissioner for Transportation of Enugu State, Chief Mathias Ekweremadu, who passed away yesterday. “It is my prayer that Almighty God grants Senator Ekweremadu, his family, and the government and people of Enugu State solace as they mourn the passing of Chief Mathias, who was a passionate public servant that served his people at various levels with distinction.” Vanguard News Nigeria The Deputy President of the Senate, Ike Ekweremadu, has expressed sadness over the death of Mrs Ann Nnaji, the wife of Sen. Gilbert Nnaji. September 10, 2017 In "News" PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has expressed heartfelt condolences to the family and the people of Katsina State over the death of Senator Mahmud Kanti-Bello. August 30, 2017 In "News" SENATE President Bukola Saraki and his deputy, Senator Ike Ekweremadu, have expressed deep sadness over the sudden death of their colleague, Senator Ali Wakili. March 18, 2018 In "News"